## The Buzz Around Savage Hulk

Marvel's upcoming film _Spider-Man: Brand New Day_, set for release on July 31, 2026, has fans buzzing over the possible appearance of the Savage Hulk. While nothing is officially confirmed, leaks from a toy list and behind-the-scenes images have sparked speculation about which version of Bruce Banner’s alter ego will appear and how he might affect the story.

The Savage Hulk is one of the most primal and uncontrollable versions of Bruce Banner. Unlike Smart Hulk, he is driven by raw emotion, acts impulsively, and lacks the reasoning and moral awareness of his calmer counterparts. This makes him a powerful but unpredictable force, especially in crowded urban environments where his presence could cause significant destruction.

## Hulk and Spider-Man’s Comic History

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/634e79e1-69eb-4637-b678-a5ea54674184/tumblr_e4e5992377d16409bc4d84f1d14de3d2_51ec7a56_1280.jpg?format=original)

Hulk and Spider-Man share a long and complicated history in the comics. Their encounters often highlight the contrast between Hulk’s brute strength and Spider-Man’s agility and intellect. They have teamed up in the past, but those meetings frequently devolve into conflicts, emphasizing how difficult it can be to contain a hero with such raw power. In the MCU, their paths have crossed briefly in _Avengers: Infinity War_ and _Avengers: Endgame_, but they have not had extended interactions.

The MCU has primarily featured Smart Hulk, who balances Banner’s intellect with immense strength. Introducing the Savage Hulk would dramatically shift this dynamic, bringing a more unpredictable and destructive version into the mix. Spider-Man would need to protect civilians while trying to restrain a nearly unstoppable force.

## Potential Story Implications

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/f8eec5d4-74d8-43d2-b550-f4b6bc30391e/5sM44xqAeeTksHWjgYLuzT.png?format=original)

Rumors also suggest that Frank Castle, the Punisher, could play a role in tracking Hulk. If true, this sets up a tense triangle with Spider-Man, who would likely intervene to defend a former ally he fought alongside in _Endgame_. This could explore complex moral questions about how to handle a threat that is also a hero.

The inclusion of Savage Hulk could raise the stakes, increase tension, and challenge Spider-Man in ways he has not faced before. It would offer the chance for more intense action sequences and character development, showing how Peter Parker can handle threats bigger than himself in both strength and ethical complexity.

Whether the rumors are accurate or not, speculation alone has fans eager for the film. A Savage Hulk in _Spider-Man: Brand New Day_ promises explosive action, moral dilemmas, and dynamic character interactions, marking a potentially major chapter in the MCU’s evolving story.

Do you want to see Savage Hulk in the MCU?